HEADWORD: Hellespont
<hw>Hel"les*pont</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Hellespontus</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ the mythological Helle, daughter
of Athamas + <?/ sea.]</ety> <def>A narrow strait between Europe and
Asia, now called the <altname>Daradanelles</altname>. It connects the
Aegean Sea and the sea of Marmora.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

